1 AN ACT relating to education and declaring an emergency.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 156 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Department" means the Kentucky Department of Education; and
7 (b) "Principal" means a person who:
8 1. Is the primary administrator and instructional leader of a public
9 school or program;
10 2. Supervises students and school employees; and
11 3. Is selected by the district's superintendent pursuant to KRS 160.345.
12 (2) There is hereby established the principal leadership development practicum to
13 provide all new principals within the first four (4) years of experience in the
14 position with leadership development training. It is the intent of the General
15 Assembly to ensure that a school district or principal incurs no cost for the
16 participation in the practicum and the principal receives a stipend toward the cost
17 of the third year of the practicum. The Kentucky Department of Education shall
18 develop and operate the practicum, subject to the following provisions:
19 (a) The practicum shall operate based on cohorts of new principals and offer
20 four (4) years of leadership development training with specific requirements
21 in each year. The department shall annually establish a calendar for the
22 operation of the practicum;
23 (b) Each year's cohort of new principals shall consist of those people who first
24 became principals by September 1 of each year;
25 (c) The department shall establish the minimum requirements for successful
26 completion of each year, including hours of instruction or specific work
27 products;
Page 1 of 35
SB000490.100 - 1215 - XXXX 4/14/2026 1:59 PM Vetoed and Overridden

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 4/VO
1 (d) The first and second year of the practicum shall provide professional
2 learning and mentorship supports to new principals, subject to the
3 following:
4 1. The mentors shall have significant and successful experience as a
5 principal and may be currently employed in a school district or retired.
6 The mentors shall provide ongoing support to the new principals
7 through the first and second school year with regular personal
8 sessions to provide individualized support to the new principal;
9 2. The mentorship shall also provide the cohort of new principals an
10 opportunity to build a peer support network;
11 3. The professional learning provided by the department shall be aligned
12 to the most recent professional standards adopted by the National
13 Policy Board for Educational Administration and include, at a
14 minimum, the following topics:
15 a. Personnel evaluation and feedback;
16 b. School-based decision making and school councils;
17 c. Implementation of instructional leadership, high-quality
18 instructional materials, and curriculum alignment;
19 d. Assessment and accountability;
20 e. Multitiered systems of support;
21 f. Services for exceptional children and youth; and
22 g. School safety; and
23 4. Professional learning under subparagraph 3. of this paragraph shall
24 utilize any existing trainings required in administrative regulation or
25 statute or developed by the department. Additional professional
26 learning developed by the department shall first be approved by the
27 Kentucky Board of Education;
Page 2 of 35
SB000490.100 - 1215 - XXXX 4/14/2026 1:59 PM Vetoed and Overridden

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 4/VO
1 (e) The third year of the practicum shall require, as funds are available, that
2 the new principal participate in an intensive leadership program during the
3 summer with follow-up sessions throughout the following year. The
4 leadership program shall be established by the department in partnership
5 with the Kentucky Chamber Foundation. A new principal shall be exempted
6 from the requirements of this paragraph if:
7 1. The new principal misses the intensive leadership program during the
8 summer due to illness or an emergency;
9 2. The absence is approved by the superintendent of the school district in
10 which the new principal is employed; and
11 3. The new principal completes an alternative program established by the
12 department; and
13 (f) The fourth year of the practicum shall not be mandatory but shall provide
14 high-level leadership training options for new principals. The department
15 shall establish the standards for training providers and the trainings under
16 this paragraph, including the number of hours required. The department
17 shall maintain a list of training providers who are eligible to provide the
18 high-level leadership training and make it available to new principals; and
19 (g) After the fourth year, each principal shall continue leadership development
20 through the effective instructional leadership program established in
21 Section 2 of this Act.
22 (3) A principal may submit the participant hours of instruction that the principal
23 earns under this section during a year toward the twenty-one (21) participant
24 hours required by the effective instructional leadership program established in
25 Section 2 of this Act. The department shall grant program credit for the verified
26 hours the principal submits.
27 (4) If a person discontinues serving as a principal during the first four (4) years of
