7 Section 8. KRS 160.210 is amended to read as follows:
8 (1) In independent school districts, the members of the school board shall be elected
9 from the district at large. In county school districts, members shall be elected from
10 divisions.
11 (2) The board of education of each county school district shall[, not later than July 1,
12 1940,] divide its district into five (5) divisions containing integral voting precincts
13 and as equal in population insofar as is practicable. In[ first] dividing the county
14 district into divisions the board shall, if more than one (1) of its members reside in
15 one (1) division, determine by lot which member from that division shall represent
16 that division, and which members shall represent the divisions in which no member
17 resides. The members so determined to represent divisions in which no member
18 resides shall be considered the members from those divisions until their terms
19 expire, and thereafter the members from those divisions shall be nominated and
20 elected as provided in KRS 160.200 and 160.220 to 160.250.
21 (3) Any changes made in division boundary lines shall be to make divisions as equal in
22 population and containing integral voting precincts insofar as is practical. No
23 change may be made in division boundary lines less than five (5) years after the last
24 change in any division lines, except in case of merger of districts, a change in
25 territory due to annexation, or to allow compliance with KRS 117.055(2).
26 (4) (a) Notwithstanding the provisions of subsection (3) of this section, if one
27 hundred (100) residents of a county school district division petition the
