13 Section 13. KRS 304.50-055 is amended to read as follows:
14 (1) As used in this section, "nationally recognized statistical rating organization" or
15 "NRSRO" means a credit rating agency approved by the United States Securities
16 and Exchange Commission to provide assessments of the creditworthiness of
17 financial instruments.
18 (2) A workers' compensation self-insured group shall establish plans for premium
19 payment, determination and collection of assessments, and for declaration and
20 payment of dividends or other disbursements, which shall be filed for prior
21 approval with the commissioner. Any change in the plans for premium payment,
22 assessments, or dividends shall be filed for prior approval with the commissioner.
23 Approval of plans for assessments and dividends does not constitute approval of
24 any particular assessment or dividend by the commissioner.
25 (3) Prior to the inception of each group member's self-insurance year, the trustees shall
26 collect from that member at least twenty-five percent (25%) of the estimated
27 premium for the ensuing year, except that in the case of a self-insured group formed
Page 25 of 35
SB000490.100 - 1215 - XXXX 4/14/2026 1:59 PM Vetoed and Overridden

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 4/VO
1 by governmental entities twenty-five percent (25%) of the estimated premium for
2 the ensuing year shall be collected no later than thirty (30) days after the beginning
3 of the self-insured group's self-insurance year. The balance of the estimated
4 premium shall be collected in either quarterly or monthly installments as set forth in
5 the enabling documents described in KRS 304.50-030(2)(b) or 304.50-060(2)(b).
6 Each group member's payroll shall be audited annually and an adjustment to
7 premium shall be made accordingly.
8 (4) A disbursement from a workers' compensation self-insured group fund shall be for
9 a purpose related to the self-insured group. A dividend shall not be approved or
10 paid until at least thirty-six (36) months after the expiration of the self-insurance
11 year and shall be paid from surplus funds not required for payment of claims or
12 other liabilities. The dividends shall be paid or credited to members according to the
13 reasonable classifications the trustees may establish. A dividend shall not be paid
14 which unfairly discriminates between members of the same classifications. A
15 dividend plan shall specify whether past group members are eligible for the
16 dividend. Payment of a dividend under a dividend plan shall not be made unless the
17 self-insured group has notified the commissioner of its intent to make a dividend
18 payment at least thirty (30) days prior to the payment, and the commissioner has not
19 disapproved the payment within that time.
20 (5) The formula to be used for collection of assessments shall be determined by the
21 trustees and approved by the commissioner. Assessments shall be fair and equitable
22 and shall not unfairly discriminate between members of the same classification.
23 (6) A trustee, fiscal agent, or service organization shall not utilize an asset of the self-
24 insured group for a purpose unrelated to workers' compensation. The trustees shall
25 maintain cash or cash equivalent accounts as may be prudently necessary to pay
26 expenses without having to liquidate long-term investments.
