1 SECTION 14. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 164 IS CREATED TO
2 READ AS FOLLOWS:
3 (1) There is established a Center of American Civics at the University of Kentucky.
4 The board of trustees for the University of Kentucky may rename the center
5 consistent with its philanthropic naming governance procedures.
6 (2) The center shall:
7 (a) Foster a deeper understanding of the structures and institutions of federal,
8 state, and local government;
9 (b) Further the understanding of the principles and philosophies that
10 contributed to the foundation and development of the United States and the
11 Commonwealth of Kentucky;
12 (c) Promote civil discourse and constructive debate;
13 (d) Enhance education in the fields of politics, economics, philosophy, law,
14 American history, American government, rule of law, and other related
15 fields as appropriate, with a focus on the rights and responsibilities of
16 American citizenship; fundamental democratic principles; and the ways in
17 which those principles are expressed in and through our federal, state, and
18 local institutions;
19 (e) Provide nonpartisan resources to students, faculty, state government
20 agencies, educators, and the general public regarding civic affairs;
21 (f) Foster civic engagement through full and fair discussions that promote civil
22 dialogue among those holding conflicting points of view; and
23 (g) Assist in ensuring that the University of Kentucky serves as a robust
24 marketplace of ideas for all students and faculty.
25 (3) In order to carry out the purposes set forth in subsection (2) of this section, the
26 provost of the University of Kentucky may:
27 (a) Name an executive director and otherwise establish governance structure
Page 30 of 35
SB000490.100 - 1215 - XXXX 4/14/2026 1:59 PM Vetoed and Overridden

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 4/VO
1 for the center;
2 (b) Develop academic guidelines, course offerings, potential internships and
3 other relevant experiences for students and the general public;
4 (c) Facilitate events, including sponsoring public lectures;
5 (d) Develop a partnership between the center and the Patterson School of
6 Diplomacy at the University of Kentucky; and
7 (e) Take other actions as appropriate.
8 (4) The center may be physically housed in the J. David Rosenberg College of Law
9 on the campus of the University of Kentucky.
10 (5) The center shall operate as an independent academic unit within the University
11 of Kentucky.
12 (6) Any funds appropriated to the center shall not supplant any existing state funding
13 or private or external donations to the University of Kentucky. Appropriated
14 funds and all private and external donations to the center may only be used for
15 operation of the center in conformance with this section.
16 SECTION 15. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 164 IS CREATED TO
17 READ AS FOLLOWS:
18 (1) The McConnell Center shall be redesignated as an independent academic unit
19 within the University of Louisville. The University of Louisville shall provide
20 adequate administrative space for the center if space does not currently exist.
21 (2) The center shall pursue all of the following goals:
22 (a) Promote the McConnell Center’s core principles of leadership, scholarship,
23 and service;
24 (b) Prepare top undergraduate students to become future leaders;
25 (c) Offer civic education programs for teachers, students, and the public; and
26 (d) Conduct strategic leadership development for the United States Army.
27 (3) In order to carry out the purposes set forth in subsection (b), the center is
