2 SECTION 16. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 164 IS CREATED TO
3 READ AS FOLLOWS:
4 The McConnell Center at the University of Louisville and the Center of American
5 Civics at the University of Kentucky shall develop materials and curricula for a degree
6 program that meets the requirements of this section and distribute the materials and
7 curricula developed to each public institution of higher education in this state. The
8 curricula shall be for a course of instruction that is three (3) semester hours, or the
9 equivalent, in American government or American history that provides a
10 comprehensive overview of the major events and turning points of American history
11 and government and, at a minimum, includes:
12 (1) An understanding of the United States Constitution in its entirety;
13 (2) An understanding of the Declaration of Independence in its entirety;
14 (3) An understanding of a minimum of five (5) essays from the Federalist Papers in
15 their entirety as selected by the course instructor;
16 (4) An understanding of the Emancipation Proclamation in its entirety;
17 (5) An understanding of the Gettysburg Address in its entirety; and
18 (6) Other documents foundational to the American Civil Rights movement.
19 Section 17. Notwithstanding any other statute to the contrary, for any large
20 school district that has seven board of education members on the effective date of this
21 section of this Act, the term of those members shall terminate on December 31, 2026. All
22 five elected members established under Section 8 of this Act shall be elected at the next
23 regular election following the effective date of this section of this Act. Within ten days of
24 January 1, 2027, the superintendent of the school district shall call a meeting of the newly
25 elected board of education for the purpose of organizing the board of education.
26 Notwithstanding the standard term of office for members of a board of education, the
27 members initially elected for Division Four and Division Five established in Section 9 of
Page 33 of 35
SB000490.100 - 1215 - XXXX 4/14/2026 1:59 PM Vetoed and Overridden

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 4/VO
1 this Act shall be for a two year term with subsequent terms being a standard four year
2 term. Members initially elected for Divisions One, Two, and Three established in Section
3 9 of this Act shall be for a standard four year term.
4 Section 18. (1) Notwithstanding any statute to the contrary, for any large
5 school district that has seven board of education members on the effective date of this
6 section of this Act, the assignment of the seven members to the five divisions shall be as
7 provided under this section until the five members elected under Section 17 of this Act
8 take office.
9 (2) For any division in which:
10 (a) Only one current board of education member resides, that member shall
11 represent that division;
12 (b) Two or more current board of education members reside, the member
13 representing that division shall be selected by drawing lots among those resident
14 members; and
15 (c) No current board of education member resides, the member representing that
16 division shall be selected by drawing lots among those members not already representing
17 another division.
18 (3) Any remaining member shall represent the district at large for the remainder
19 of his or her term.
20 (4) Any further setting of divisions or setting of the member representing a
21 division shall be conducted in accordance with Section 8 of this Act and as otherwise
22 provided for in statute.
23 Section 19. Notwithstanding the eligibility requirements established in
24 subsection (2)(h) of Section 7 of this Act, a person who was elected or appointed to a
25 board of education prior to the effective date of Section 7 of this Act shall remain eligible
26 for the office for the remainder of the term to which he or she was elected or appointed.
27 The person shall not be subsequently eligible to serve a new term on a board of
Page 34 of 35
SB000490.100 - 1215 - XXXX 4/14/2026 1:59 PM Vetoed and Overridden

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 4/VO
1 education, or eligible to be a candidate for election or appointment to a new term on a
2 board of education, unless that person meets all the requirements of Section 7 of this Act.
3 Section 20. By November 1, 2026, the Kentucky Department of Education shall
4 submit to the Legislative Research Commission for referral to the appropriate interim
5 joint committees a plan for the implementation of each year of the practicum described in
6 Section 1 of this Act that includes any minimum requirements for successful completion
7 that the department will require and any statutory amendments the department needs for
8 implementation of the practicum.
9 Section 21. Whereas timely elections and appointments are critically important
10 to the operation of large school districts, an emergency is declared to exist, and Sections
11 5 to 13 and Sections 17 to 19 of this Act take effect upon its passage and approval by the
12 Governor or upon its otherwise becoming a law.
